    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "So this is somewhat related to this issue. I need to be able to grab what's been typed into a search box and then pipe that into a different index's search box and run the search. I can change search.helper.state.query, but it doesn't affect the DOM or run a new search. Is there a method I'm missing or some way I can manually initiate a search with a new query?\r\n\r\nFor context, I'm trying to put together multiple searches, but have only one visible at a time. When I switch index, I want to carry over the current typed value in the search bar to the index that I'm switching to's search bar.",
